ralegal Program. Gail graduated from Winona State University with a Bachelors of Social Work and has practiced immigrant and refugee social work with Neighborhood House, Highland Family Center, West Seventh Community Center, and the Intercultural Mutual Assistance Association in Rochester. At ILCM, Ms. Martinson provides representation to Dreamers in applying for Consideration for Deferred Action for Childhood Arrivals.'),(4509,447,'_staff_members_12_bio','field_56ce5c01ab454'),(4510,447,'staff_members_13_name','Isbely McKeen'),(4511,447,'_staff_members_13_name','field_56ce5bdaab452'),(4512,447,'staff_members_13_position','BIA ACCREDITED REPRESENTATIVE/LEGAL ASSISTANT '),(4513,447,'_staff_members_13_position','field_56ce5bebab453'),(4514,447,'staff_members_13_bio','Isbely graduated from the University of Zulia, Venezuela in 1994 with a Bachelors Degree in Law. From 1991-1994, Ms. McKeen worked as a clerk at the First Judicial Municipal Court of the State of Zulia. She first became involved with ILCM as an intern in 2011 and was brought on full-time to assist with Deferred Action after completing the paralegal program at Inver Hills Community College in 2012. Currently, Ms. McKeen represents clients with U-visa, VAWA, and Removal of Conditions applications. '),(4515,447,'_staff_members_13_bio','field_56ce5c01ab454'),(4516,447,'staff_members_14_name','Robyn Meyer-Thompson, Esq. '),(4517,447,'_staff_members_14_name','field_56ce5bdaab452'),(4518,447,'staff_members_14_position','STAFF ATTORNEY'),(4519,447,'_staff_members_14_position','field_56ce5bebab453'),(4520,447,'staff_members_14_bio','Robyn graduated summa cum laude from William Mitchell College of Law in 2014 and received the Student of Merit Award for her service with clients through the Civil Advocacy and Immigration Law Clinics at William Mitchell. She earned her undergraduate degree in 2009 from the College of St. Benedict with majors in Spanish and Political Science. From 2009-2011, Robyn taught eighth grade U.S. history through the Teach for America program in Roma, Texas. During law school, Robyn worked at ILCM and Southern MN Regional Services on U visa, VAWA, and asylum applications. Prior to joining the ILCM team, Robyn served as the Immigrant Health Law Specialist at Health Access MN, focusing on noncitizen eligibility for health insurance in Minnesota. At ILCM, Robyn represents detained clients in removal proceedings and clients submitting affirmative applications for relief.'),(4521,447,'_staff_members_14_bio','field_56ce5c01ab454'),(4522,447,'staff_members_15_name','Meghan Pierce'),(4523,447,'_staff_members_15_name','field_56ce5bdaab452'),(4524,447,'staff_members_15_position','DEVELOPMENT COORDINATOR'),(4525,447,'_staff_members_15_position','field_56ce5bebab453'),(4526,447,'staff_members_15_bio','Meghan graduated magna cum laude from the George Washington University in 2014, where she received a Bachelors degree in International Affairs and Gender Studies. Prior to joining ILCM, Meg held program assistant positions at Vital Voices Global Partnership and the Institute for Global and International Studies in Washington, DC.'),(4527,447,'_staff_members_15_bio','field_56ce5c01ab454'),(4528,447,'staff_members_16_name','Sandra Portilla'),(4529,447,'_staff_members_16_name','field_56ce5bdaab452'),(4530,447,'staff_members_16_position','RECEPTIONIST AND VOLUNTEER COORDINATOR'),(4531,447,'_staff_members_16_position','field_56ce5bebab453'),(4532,447,'staff_members_16_bio','Sandra Portilla is a liberal arts student at Minneapolis Community and Technical College, majoring in history. Sandra is fluent in Spanish and English, and has four years of previous customer service experience. She is enthusiastic about her role as receptionist because of the history she has with ILCM Sandra and her family were assisted by ILCM attorneys in obtaining their work permits and residency. Having had this important experience, she is proud to be able to provide the same life-changing services to other individuals and families. '),(4533,447,'_staff_members_16_bio','field_56ce5c01ab454'),(4534,447,'staff_members_17_name','Laueh Roland'),(4535,447,'_staff_members_17_name','field_56ce5bdaab452'),(4536,447,'staff_members_17_position','LEGAL ASSISTANT'),(4537,447,'_staff_members_17_position','field_56ce5bebab453'),(4538,447,'staff_members_17_bio','Laueh joined ILCM in 2011 and works with our refugee project. Laueh works with ILCM\'s affiliate office, the Neighborhood House, and is fluent in both English and Karen.'),(4539,447,'_staff_members_17_bio','field_56ce5c01ab454'),(4540,447,'staff_members_18_name','Stephanie Rosario Alvarez'),(4541,447,'_staff_members_18_name','field_56ce5bdaab452'),(4542,447,'staff_members_18_position','ADMINISTRATIVE ASSISTANT'),(4543,447,'_staff_members_18_position','field_56ce5bebab453'),(4544,447,'staff_members_18_bio','Stephanie earned a degree in Technical and Business Administration from Centro de Bachillerato Tecnologico y de Servicios #114 in Mexico. She has over twelve years of customer service experience in both the medical and legal fields and has worked at ILCM since 2010.'),(4545,447,'_staff_members_18_bio','field_56ce5c01ab454'),(4546,447,'staff_members_19_name','Bao Thao, Esq.'),(4547,447,'_staff_members_19_name','field_56ce5bdaab452'),(4548,447,'staff_members_19_position','STAFF ATTORNEY'),(4549,447,'_staff_members_19_position','field_56ce5bebab453'),(4550,447,'staff_members_19_bio','Bao is an alumna of St. Norbert College where she earned a Bachelor of Business Administration degree, majoring in International Business and Language Area Studies. After graduating from St. Norbert, Bao went to Saitama Prefecture in Japan for three years to work as an assistant language teacher through the Japan Exchange and Teaching (JET) Program. Prior to starting law school at the University of St. Thomas, Bao worked for Mid-Minnesota Legal Services in Minneapolis in an intake capacity. Prior to graduating in 2010, Bao was involved with the Immigration Law Practice Group, one of several legal clinics offered through the University of St. Thomass clinic program. Bao worked in various areas, most recently in the financial services industry, before joining ILCM in July 2014 as a staff attorney. Bao is fluent in Hmong and is enthusiastic about helping ILCM\'s services better reach the Hmong community of Minnesota. '),(4551,447,'_staff_members_19_bio','field_56ce5c01ab454'),(4552,447,'staff_members_20_name',''),(4553,447,'_staff_members_20_name','field_56ce5bdaab452'),(4554,447,'staff_members_20_position',''),(4555,447,'_staff_members_20_position','field_56ce5bebab453'),(4556,447,'staff_members_20_bio',''),(4557,447,'_staff_members_20_bio','field_56ce5c01ab454'),(4558,447,'staff_members','21'),(4559,447,'_staff_members','field_56ce5bc8ab451'),(4560,195,'staff_members_18_name','Stephanie Rosario Alvarez'),(4561,195,'_staff_members_18_name','field_56ce5bdaab452'),(4562,195,'staff_members_18_position','ADMINISTRATIVE ASSISTANT'),(4563,195,'_staff_members_18_position','field_56ce5bebab453'),(4564,195,'staff_members_18_bio','Stephanie earned a degree in Technical and Business Administration from Centro de Bachillerato Tecnologico y de Servicios #114 in Mexico. She has over twelve years of customer service experience in both the medical and legal fields and has worked at ILCM since 2010.'),(4565,195,'_staff_members_18_bio','field_56ce5c01ab454'),(4566,195,'staff_members_19_name','Bao Thao, Esq.'),(4567,195,'_staff_members_19_name','field_56ce5bdaab452'),(4568,195,'staff_members_19_position','STAFF ATTORNEY'),(4569,195,'_staff_members_19_position','field_56ce5bebab453'),(4570,195,'staff_members_19_bio','Bao is an alumna of St. Norbert College where she earned a Bachelor of Business Administration degree, majoring in International Business and Language Area Studies. After graduating from St. Norbert, Bao went to Saitama Prefecture in Japan for three years to work as an assistant language teacher through the 