ions at Vital Voices Global Partnership and the Institute for Global and International Studies in Washington, DC.'),(4673,448,'_staff_members_15_bio','field_56ce5c01ab454'),(4674,448,'staff_members_16_name','Sandra Portilla'),(4675,448,'_staff_members_16_name','field_56ce5bdaab452'),(4676,448,'staff_members_16_position','RECEPTIONIST AND VOLUNTEER COORDINATOR'),(4677,448,'_staff_members_16_position','field_56ce5bebab453'),(4678,448,'staff_members_16_bio','Sandra Portilla is a liberal arts student at Minneapolis Community and Technical College, majoring in history. Sandra is fluent in Spanish and English, and has four years of previous customer service experience. She is enthusiastic about her role as receptionist because of the history she has with ILCM Sandra and her family were assisted by ILCM attorneys in obtaining their work permits and residency. Having had this important experience, she is proud to be able to provide the same life-changing services to other individuals and families. '),(4679,448,'_staff_members_16_bio','field_56ce5c01ab454'),(4680,448,'staff_members_17_name','Laueh Roland'),(4681,448,'_staff_members_17_name','field_56ce5bdaab452'),(4682,448,'staff_members_17_position','LEGAL ASSISTANT'),(4683,448,'_staff_members_17_position','field_56ce5bebab453'),(4684,448,'staff_members_17_bio','Laueh joined ILCM in 2011 and works with our refugee project. Laueh works with ILCM\'s affiliate office, the Neighborhood House, and is fluent in both English and Karen.'),(4685,448,'_staff_members_17_bio','field_56ce5c01ab454'),(4686,448,'staff_members_18_name','Stephanie Rosario Alvarez'),(4687,448,'_staff_members_18_name','field_56ce5bdaab452'),(4688,448,'staff_members_18_position','ADMINISTRATIVE ASSISTANT'),(4689,448,'_staff_members_18_position','field_56ce5bebab453'),(4690,448,'staff_members_18_bio','Stephanie earned a degree in Technical and Business Administration from Centro de Bachillerato Tecnologico y de Servicios #114 in Mexico. She has over twelve years of customer service experience in both the medical and legal fields and has worked at ILCM since 2010.'),(4691,448,'_staff_members_18_bio','field_56ce5c01ab454'),(4692,448,'staff_members_19_name','Bao Thao, Esq.'),(4693,448,'_staff_members_19_name','field_56ce5bdaab452'),(4694,448,'staff_members_19_position','STAFF ATTORNEY'),(4695,448,'_staff_members_19_position','field_56ce5bebab453'),(4696,448,'staff_members_19_bio','Bao is an alumna of St. Norbert College where she earned a Bachelor of Business Administration degree, majoring in International Business and Language Area Studies. After graduating from St. Norbert, Bao went to Saitama Prefecture in Japan for three years to work as an assistant language teacher through the Japan Exchange and Teaching (JET) Program. Prior to starting law school at the University of St. Thomas, Bao worked for Mid-Minnesota Legal Services in Minneapolis in an intake capacity. Prior to graduating in 2010, Bao was involved with the Immigration Law Practice Group, one of several legal clinics offered through the University of St. Thomass clinic program. Bao worked in various areas, most recently in the financial services industry, before joining ILCM in July 2014 as a staff attorney. Bao is fluent in Hmong and is enthusiastic about helping ILCM\'s services better reach the Hmong community of Minnesota. '),(4697,448,'_staff_members_19_bio','field_56ce5c01ab454'),(4698,448,'staff_members_20_name','Sarah Trautman'),(4699,448,'_staff_members_20_name','field_56ce5bdaab452'),(4700,448,'staff_members_20_position','DEVELOPMENT ASSOCIATE'),(4701,448,'_staff_members_20_position','field_56ce5bebab453'),(4702,448,'staff_members_20_bio','Sarah graduated magna cum laude from Carleton College in 2013 with majors in English and Biology. While in college and before working at ILCM, she followed her interests in community building and the outdoors to Utah, Maine, and Colorado where she worked as direct care staff at a group home, wilderness therapy, and a homeless shelter.'),(4703,448,'_staff_members_20_bio','field_56ce5c01ab454'),(4704,448,'staff_members_21_name','Tammy Villegas'),(4705,448,'_staff_members_21_name','field_56ce5bdaab452'),(4706,448,'staff_members_21_position','INTAKE SPECIALIST'),(4707,448,'_staff_members_21_position','field_56ce5bebab453'),(4708,448,'staff_members_21_bio','Tammy graduated from the College of St. Benedict with a degree in social work. She came to ILCM from the Dodge Nature Preschool where she spent her time educating children about the wonders of the natural world. She has spent over 15 years working with nonprofits in the areas of community organizing and outreach. She spent significant time in California working in nonprofits including La Clinica San Pedro in South Central LA, the LA Catholic Worker, and the headquarters and field offices of the United Farm Workers throughout California. Tammy joined ILCM in June 2008 and is excited to continue in a role that helps provide a voice to all people.'),(4709,448,'_staff_members_21_bio','field_56ce5c01ab454'),(4710,448,'staff_members','22'),(4711,448,'_staff_members','field_56ce5bc8ab451'),(4712,195,'staff_members_21_name','Tammy Villegas'),(4713,195,'_staff_members_21_name','field_56ce5bdaab452'),(4714,195,'staff_members_21_position','INTAKE SPECIALIST'),(4715,195,'_staff_members_21_position','field_56ce5bebab453'),(4716,195,'staff_members_21_bio','Tammy graduated from the College of St. Benedict with a degree in social work. She came to ILCM from the Dodge Nature Preschool where she spent her time educating children about the wonders of the natural world. She has spent over 15 years working with nonprofits in the areas of community organizing and outreach. She spent significant time in California working in nonprofits including La Clinica San Pedro in South Central LA, the LA Catholic Worker, and the headquarters and field offices of the United Farm Workers throughout California. Tammy joined ILCM in June 2008 and is excited to conti